</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:02
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='471000' id='t-471000'>So why do economists fall in love</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='474000' id='t-474000'>with authoritarian governments?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='477000' id='t-477000'>One reason is the East Asian Model.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='479000' id='t-479000'>In East Asia,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='481000' id='t-481000'>we have had successful economic growth stories</span>
